name: Squid with Mixed Vegetables
author: nt_bella
summary: A quick and easy recipe for squid with summer vegetables like zucchini, bell pepper, and tomatoes. You can speed up the preparation of this quick dinner even more if you use squid rings. If you are using frozen squid, thaw before cooking.
ingredients: salt and freshly ground black pepper
1  red bell pepper - cored, seeded and thinly sliced
1 pound squid, cleaned and sliced into rings
directions: Heat olive oil in a skillet and cook onion until softened, about 3 minutes
Add bell pepper and zucchini and cook until softened, 3 to 5 minutes
Stir in tomatoes, garlic, salt, and black pepper
Pour in white wine and bring to a boil
Add squid and cook until squid is just cooked through, about 5 minutes
Sprinkle with chopped basil to serve
